<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1315795" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Amaka-Igwe.jpg?resize=640%2C292&#038;ssl=1" alt="Amaka Igwe, google doodle" width="640" height="292" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Amaka-Igwe.jpg?w=842&amp;ssl=1 842w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Amaka-Igwe.jpg?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Amaka-Igwe.jpg?resize=768%2C350&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Amaka-Igwe.jpg?resize=58%2C26&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Amaka-Igwe.jpg?resize=260%2C119&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Amaka-Igwe.jpg?resize=200%2C91&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Amaka-Igwe.jpg?resize=560%2C255&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Late veteran Nollywood filmmaker, Amaka Igwe, has been honoured with a Google Doodle on her 57th posthumous birthday. A Google Doodle is a special, temporary alteration of the logo on Google’s homepages intended to commemorate holidays, events, achievements and notable historical figures. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the doodle went live on Thursday as an honour of late Igwe’s contributions to Nollywood. She was a Nigerian filmmaker and broadcasting executive. Igwe was the owner of Top Radio 90.9 Lagos and Amaka Igwe Studios. She was recognised as one of the second-generation filmmakers who helped begin the video film era of Nigerian cinema. She remained a prominent figure in the industry until her death in 2014. Igwe hit national limelight as the writer and producer of award-winning TV soap ‘Checkmate’ and its offshoot ‘Fuji House of Commotion’. Her Nollywood projects include ‘Rattle snake’ and ‘Violated’, which set Amaka Igwe Studios apart in the Video film era of Nigerian cinema. (NAN) VANGUARD Amaka Igwe remembered: Silence enveloped the expansive Expo hall of Eko and Suites’, Lagos when Amaka Igwe, who died last year was honoured with ‘Lifetime Achievement’ award . The award was presented by none other than Nollywood veteran actor-turned-politician, Richard Mofe-Damijo, who saluted the late film maker for her outstanding… March 13, 2015 In "Entertainment" Since legendary Nollywood movie-maker, Amaka Igwe passed on, Tuesday, many top actors have been coming forth to reveal what impact the woman played in their careers. May 4, 2014 In "Entertainment" Google on Sunday celebrated Nigerian novelist Buchi Emecheta with its Doodle on what would have been her 75th birthday. July 21, 2019 In "Just Human"